{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e97f178f-61b1-425f-97e3-3187055a6b65","content":"**net6.0 is not supported in MSTest v4.** It dropped `net6.0` and `net7.0` — you must target **net8.0** or later.\n\nUpdate your `TestProject.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\nBeyond the TFM change, MSTest v4 has several breaking API changes (e.g., `Assert.ThrowsException` → `Assert.ThrowsExactly`, async lifecycle methods, sealed attributes). Would you like me to run the full migration on your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4b502cba-af76-4cd8-80d5-5e206fb8ebac","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about MSTest v4 migration and whether net6.0 will still be supported. I have a skill for this: `migrate-mstest-v3-to-v4`. Let me invoke it since it covers dropped TFMs.","outputTokens":216,"requestId":"7C10:9F1F0:185C97C:1BB0301:69F95DFA"},"id":"980a12fd-2e3b-4ef5-bc30-d2b248ea1edf","timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:03:28.719Z","parentId":"8baf6bd1-b536-4aaf-b930-5b37b77501e2"}
